Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.56,0:00:05.77,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Guys, guys!\N Just listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.77,0:00:09.82,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the hell is it? \NCan you just be quiet already?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.82,0:00:12.11,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I was thinking about it last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.11,0:00:17.83,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,So, if you ate human meat, \Ndo you think it would taste good or bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.60,0:00:21.85,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,No, Mista.\N Let's {\i1}not{\i0} talk about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.85,0:00:24.87,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Why would you bring up \Nthat kind of shit {\i1}now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:27.52,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Fuck off!\N Go eat by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.30,0:00:39.72,Main,Gold Experience Requiem,0,0,0,,Muda Muda Muda Muda!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.29,0:00:46.23,Main,Gold Experience Requiem,0,0,0,,You'll never arrive at your destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:50.30,Main,Gold Experience Requiem,0,0,0,,More precisely, \Nyou'll never arrive at the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:53.57,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You impertinent brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.57,0:00:55.28,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Muda Muda Muda Muda!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.41,0:00:58.32,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Muda!
Comment: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:02.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Opening
Comment: 0,0:02:57.07,0:02:57.11,Main,,0,0,0,,B
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.49,0:03:01.70,Title Part 5,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(107,914)\fad(402,394)\fs60}Episodio 38  Gold Experience Requiem
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.68,0:03:03.78,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Y-You did it! Finally!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:10.14,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Your Gold Experience evolved with the arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.14,0:03:14.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I didn't get a good look{/see it clearly}, \Nso I'm not sure how you did it... {This might be the wrong way to fix it, but this line was "people die if they are killed" levels of obvious}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.46,0:03:16.92,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...but he's finally defeated!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.92,0:03:19.29,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Wait... Hold on a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.29,0:03:20.76,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Did he float up yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.28,0:03:24.72,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Hey, where is he? \NWhere is his body?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.11,0:03:28.18,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.18,0:03:30.64,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Where is he? \NFind him, Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.64,0:03:32.52,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.95,0:03:50.12,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Somehow... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.85,0:03:55.38,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...just barely... still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:56.88,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I don't know how...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.26,0:04:00.72,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,But... What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.72,0:04:07.68,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,My victory was assured\N in the vision I witnessed, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:11.35,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Just what in the world... \Nwas that Requiem?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.21,0:04:17.36,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,For now... \NI'll escape into the sewers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.36,0:04:21.78,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I still... have enough strength left for that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.55,0:04:39.90,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I... I did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.81,0:04:44.89,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Was this just good fortune?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.99,0:04:51.77,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.77,0:04:58.24,Main,Guy,0,0,0,, If you're tryna...\N s-s-sneak up an' snatch my coat...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.24,0:05:00.32,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,You got another thing comin'! {Danananaaah da da - Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.19,0:05:03.71,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,You ready to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.15,0:05:08.83,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Are ya?!\N I'm no weakling!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.77,0:05:11.59,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I'll fuck you up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.46,0:05:19.34,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Come get some, ya limp-dick bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.04,0:05:29.95,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.99,0:05:35.65,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}Come on! Come get some!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.26,0:05:38.34,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I-Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.13,0:05:41.26,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,This can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.95,0:05:44.03,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}You ain't never gonna get my coat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.03,0:05:45.03,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I can't get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.88,0:05:50.74,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,S-Someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.48,0:05:56.75,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}You'll never get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.34,0:05:56.75,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,N-Not here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.25,0:06:01.34,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I-I'm Diavolo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.34,0:06:04.28,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I can't... to a man like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.69,0:06:06.76,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I'm fading...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.09,0:06:21.23,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.42,0:06:27.03,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Why was I sleeping on this bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.03,0:06:32.19,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I fell into the river, \Nand then I went into that sewer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.19,0:06:35.86,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,Let's see... Today's date is the 25th. {Since I know this is going to get comments in QC, her entire section was intentionally edited to be brief and to the point since she's conducting an autopsy. That's why there's so much shorthand and removed words -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.86,0:06:37.93,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,11:20 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.93,0:06:39.81,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,File number 68.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.81,0:06:43.29,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,I, Dr. Monica Ultello, \Nwill be carrying out this procedure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.68,0:06:48.69,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,Subject is an adult male,\N estimated between thirty and forty years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.69,0:06:50.13,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,Identity unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.13,0:06:55.73,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,Judging by the state of his skin,\N about 48 to 54 hours since time of death. {too much removal?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.28,0:06:59.19,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,I will now begin the autopsy \Nto determine the cause of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.67,0:07:03.31,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Hey, woman... What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.19,0:07:07.15,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,{\an8}Though his body was found by the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.15,0:07:10.74,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Where am I? \NWhat am I doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.15,0:07:12.20,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,{\an8}...there doesn't appear to be any water in his lungs,\N indicating that he didn't drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.74,0:07:12.20,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Hey, woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.43,0:07:18.66,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I can't move...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.66,0:07:21.33,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,M-My fingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:22.96,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,My body...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.63,0:07:25.21,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What is happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.21,0:07:27.80,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Hey, woman!\N Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.80,0:07:29.76,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:31.13,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.99,0:07:37.39,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Why won't my body move?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.39,0:07:40.31,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,A-And this pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.31,0:07:43.23,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I-It's agony!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.81,0:07:45.39,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,{\an8}Cause of death was a\Nstab wound sustained to the liver.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.39,0:07:49.24,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,No signs of hesitation visible, \Nso suicide can be ruled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.33,0:07:53.81,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,Next, I'm going to make a small incision in the abdomen to check for abnormalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.87,0:08:00.33,Main,Monica,0,0,0,,Liver appears healthy. \NGood color.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:13.95,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,W-Was that a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.95,0:08:16.67,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Am I dreaming right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.67,0:08:17.56,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.17,0:08:20.64,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I-It's happening again. Where...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:26.98,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What time is it? \NWhere am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:30.57,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I was in the Tiber River in Rome... {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tiber}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:34.10,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,And that feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.10,0:08:38.55,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,That unimaginable pain \NI experienced in the autopsy room...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.55,0:08:40.94,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I-It felt so real...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.34,0:08:45.67,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Hello, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.05,0:08:47.65,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.65,0:08:51.17,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I just noticed you hunched over in the street... \NAre you feeling unwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.37,0:08:55.01,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Hey, stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.89,0:09:00.83,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.83,0:09:02.35,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,This isn't right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.71,0:09:05.63,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,S-Something so mundane couldn't possibly...{Implication: "A CAR CRASH?! A CAR CRASH KILLED DIAVOLO?!" -Starfish} {I love that this is similar to when Doppio almost got hit by the truck when he arrived in Sardinia - Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.25,0:09:07.90,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.99,0:09:14.20,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...Gold Experience Requiem's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:17.20,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,We have to go find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.20,0:09:20.54,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I can sense that he's still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.54,0:09:22.93,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,We can't rest easy until we know for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.93,0:09:25.00,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No, there's no need to look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.00,0:09:25.88,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.44,0:09:28.36,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.89,0:09:34.68,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I couldn't quite see Requiem's ability for myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.68,0:09:37.64,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...yet for some reason, \N I know deep in my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.64,0:09:40.63,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...that he will never arrive at his destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.19,0:09:44.45,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,More precisely, \Nhe will never arrive at the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.85,0:09:50.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The truth of his death will never come to pass...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.37,0:09:53.19,Main,Girl,0,0,0,,What's wrong, mister? \NDoes your tummy hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.66,0:09:55.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Forever more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.91,0:09:58.35,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,B-But he's still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.35,0:10:00.33,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,His is an end with no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.33,0:10:04.83,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That... is Gold Experience Requiem!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:10.08,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,H-How many times am I going to die?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.08,0:10:16.01,Thoughts,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Wh-When and where will it happen next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.01,0:10:18.05,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,S-Stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.98,0:10:21.10,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.97,0:10:24.06,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,S-Stay...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.06,0:10:27.89,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Stay the hell away from me! {Still not sure how he died here? Did the little girl kill him? - A}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:30.36,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,So we really did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:32.36,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,We're the ones who won?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:37.51,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, come on! \NLet's get back to the Colosseum!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.51,0:10:41.28,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Even though Buccellati got his soul back, \Nhe's gotta be hurting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.99,0:10:45.79,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I bet he's waiting for us at the Colosseum wondering what the hell happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:46.79,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:51.95,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Giorno, come on! \NWe gotta go to the Colosseum!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.95,0:10:55.03,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You'll heal Buccellati's wounds \Nso we can all go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.29,0:11:00.80,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yeah... Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.80,0:11:02.86,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'll be there in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.75,0:11:08.23,Narrator,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno, this is how it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.15,0:11:11.89,Narrator,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't let it trouble you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.15,0:11:18.55,Narrator,Bruno,0,0,0,,Everything we've done until this moment led us to victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.08,0:11:22.21,Narrator,Bruno,0,0,0,,Fate is a sleeping slave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.21,0:11:25.07,Narrator,Bruno,0,0,0,,A slave we were able to set free.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:27.87,Narrator,Bruno,0,0,0,,That is our victory.
Comment: 0,0:11:35.13,0:11:35.17,Main,,0,0,0,,C
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:41.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Just hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:44.95,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Taking time to {\i1}really{\i0} think about what you're eating...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:49.23,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...is connected to whether or not \Nyou're living a happy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.66,0:11:53.32,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,That's why I think it's so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.32,0:11:57.03,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Think about it! \NThere are animals who mostly eat meat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.03,0:12:00.11,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Like lions, cats, vultures, and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.11,0:12:04.93,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You won't find meat from \Ncarnivores like that at any restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:05.78,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.98,0:12:09.96,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's because it smells \Nand you can barely eat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.96,0:12:11.21,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's nasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.21,0:12:14.92,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,So, let's recap. \NCats are too nasty to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:16.19,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We still on the same page?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.19,0:12:21.19,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Even if some master chef \Nsaid it was delicious, I'd never eat cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.19,0:12:24.19,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,On the other hand, \Nhave you heard of sweetfish before?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.19,0:12:27.38,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Sweetfish don't eat bugs, just algae.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.38,0:12:29.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,They're herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.08,0:12:34.40,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Fish guts are usually way too bitter to eat, \Nbut sweetfish guts taste delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.40,0:12:36.45,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's because they're not carnivores!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.10,0:12:39.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,So putting what we know together...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.15,0:12:44.07,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...we can deduce that the meat \Nwe consider delicious comes from herbivores!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.07,0:12:46.40,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Cows! Pigs! Chickens!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.40,0:12:49.79,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The better their feed, the better they taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.79,0:12:51.49,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,And from {\i1}this{\i0} we can conclude...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.49,0:12:54.79,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...that human meat\N would taste nasty since we eat meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.79,0:12:57.95,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Well? \NWhat do you think of my answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.95,0:13:00.76,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I get it. \NI'm convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.76,0:13:05.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,That whole thing in a bunch of books\N about human meat tasting delicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.15,0:13:06.98,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...is a complete lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.98,0:13:12.18,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I, uh... I actually eat way more\N fruits and vegetables than meat, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.19,0:13:15.52,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Then you're probably pretty tasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.52,0:13:18.77,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Narancia, don't humor him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.15,0:13:22.86,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Buccellati, about time you showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:27.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You all know "Leaky-eye" Luca \Nwho controls the airport, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.27,0:13:30.22,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He was just found dead and disfigured.{Literally "found as a strange corpse". -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.22,0:13:33.62,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The capo Polpo ordered \None of us to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.62,0:13:37.43,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,That guy was a dick. \NHe had it coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.43,0:13:39.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He liked picking on the weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:41.95,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,...and he sold drugs to kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.95,0:13:45.97,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He probably took too many drugs\N and knocked himself upside the head or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:50.76,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia, you may feel that way on the inside, \Nbut don't say it out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.14,0:13:52.49,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Remember the world we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.26,0:13:55.99,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Would you like me to investigate?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.99,0:13:58.51,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,You're going to be a capo someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.51,0:14:00.99,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,There's no need for you to \Ntrouble yourself with something so trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.99,0:14:03.59,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's fine, I'll do it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:05.99,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,By the way, Fugo...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.99,0:14:08.08,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Oh, your guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.08,0:14:10.62,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He's been waiting for you all morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:13.96,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He's a civilian who runs \Na flower shop in Monsanto Plaza.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.96,0:14:15.46,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I already looked into him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.43,0:14:22.09,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He's an ordinary, responsible gentleman, \Nbut he lost his only daughter six months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.87,0:14:30.72,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Mr. Buccellati... \NAs you can see, my legs have seen better days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.72,0:14:36.22,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Normally my wife would be able to assist me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.22,0:14:39.06,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,...but today I came alone, and for that I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.06,0:14:41.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Do you pay your taxes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.75,0:14:44.53,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.33,0:14:50.82,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Do you always make sure to pay \Nthe taxes you owe to this country on time?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.79,0:14:54.51,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Of course I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.51,0:14:58.01,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I don't know what you came here to talk to me about...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.01,0:15:01.75,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...but a civilian like you shouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.75,0:15:04.32,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you properly pay your taxes...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.32,0:15:08.01,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...then you should go talk to the police \Nor another law enforcement agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:12.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The moment we begin discussing this for real...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.07,0:15:16.52,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...you'll owe the organization \Na greater debt than you can even imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.48,0:15:23.51,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I, like everyone else in this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.51,0:15:27.18,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,...worked hard to support my family... \N...believed in the law...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:30.77,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,...and raised my child to be a law-abiding citizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.36,0:15:35.02,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,She was my only daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.64,0:15:38.54,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Last September she turned seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.71,0:15:41.93,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I apologize if I'm asking too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.93,0:15:46.80,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,...but I'd like to continue this \Nconversation with you in private.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.80,0:15:49.63,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you're intent on continuing this conversation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.63,0:15:54.13,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...know that they have \Ncomplete trust in me, and I in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.13,0:15:59.43,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You're asking me to interrupt their meal \Nand tell them to go outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.43,0:16:01.06,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.05,0:16:06.77,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,This happened a few months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.39,0:16:12.79,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,My wife told me that \Nour daughter had a boyfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.79,0:16:16.72,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I heard that he was \Na young sculptor just starting out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.72,0:16:22.53,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I didn't have a problem with that, \Nbut even though he was older than my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.53,0:16:26.45,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,...he never came to \Nintroduce himself to us, her parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.45,0:16:28.71,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Admittedly, it bothered me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:31.26,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Shortly after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.47,0:16:34.61,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,...my daughter jumped from \Nthe roof of his apartment building...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.61,0:16:39.27,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,...while clutching a strange stone sculpture\N he had made, and landed in the courtyard...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.78,0:16:49.73,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry for losing my composure...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:54.20,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Why does it still hurt so much to cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:57.93,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I put my hopes in my daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.93,0:17:02.25,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,My daughter was a shining, \Nbeautiful young woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.83,0:17:05.96,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I want you to avenge her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.38,0:17:09.21,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Make that man pay for what he's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.38,0:17:12.26,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Slow down, mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:15.55,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Are you saying she was murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:20.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You think her boyfriend \Npushed her off the roof?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.27,0:17:25.10,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Whenever someone is murdered in this town, \NI hear about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.49,0:17:31.36,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,The police refused to continue \Ntheir investigation and ruled it a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.36,0:17:33.11,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Even my lawyer abandoned me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.11,0:17:36.70,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,But I know something\N only a member of her family would...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:41.80,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,My daughter would {\i1}never{\i0} commit suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.80,0:17:45.08,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Both my wife and I \Ncan say that with confidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.08,0:17:49.37,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Please! \NI want you to settle this once and for all!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.37,0:17:56.59,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Please make that bastard, whose life went uninterrupted, cry these painful tears instead of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.32,0:17:59.88,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Life is full of hardships.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.88,0:18:03.18,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You have my sympathies,\N but I can't agree to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:08.52,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Do you think we're assassins\N who would lynch just anyone for pay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.52,0:18:11.63,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Everyone in this town relies on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.63,0:18:15.13,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,I just want proper judgment to be passed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.13,0:18:16.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Proper judgment?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.02,0:18:21.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mr. florist, earlier you asked if we could speak in private.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.61,0:18:27.08,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You asked this because you knew how dangerous of a conversation it would be, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.42,0:18:34.14,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But what you said about knowing something only a member of her family would know...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.67,0:18:36.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I can't take that lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.40,0:18:43.57,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe that no one in law enforcement was moved by those words these past six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.57,0:18:46.21,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I truly can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.82,0:18:51.23,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The least I can do\N is get this boyfriend to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.23,0:18:55.67,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I won't ask for your payment \Nunless we can confirm beyond a doubt that he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.37,0:18:57.80,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Is that acceptable?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.45,0:19:01.67,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Mr. Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.41,0:19:04.62,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mista...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:07.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'd like you to handle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.07,0:19:07.91,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.29,0:19:13.50,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,What the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.25,0:19:16.21,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,...is this stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.51,0:19:28.65,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Mista, make sure you put that \Nback on its pedestal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.65,0:19:34.41,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Uh... Did I knock this stone... \N...off its pedestal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.41,0:19:36.61,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Was it here this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.61,0:19:39.21,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Be careful when you stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.21,0:19:41.82,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,You don't want to knock it to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.82,0:19:45.79,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Mista, Buccellati says we can drive you partway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.19,0:19:47.19,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.22,0:19:56.38,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mista, here's the address of his apartment building.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:59.13,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,And here's a picture of the boyfriend. {he says it in English -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.13,0:20:01.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Find him and make him talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.20,0:20:05.13,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Rough him up a bit if need be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.13,0:20:06.85,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Make sure you get a confession.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.45,0:20:08.72,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You have a tape recorder, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.72,0:20:12.71,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Yeah... But how far should I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.71,0:20:17.94,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I mean, if it turns out he's a murderer \Nand really did kill that girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.94,0:20:20.33,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We aren't assassins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.33,0:20:24.66,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Go as far as making sure he can't walk for a few years,\N then leave the rest to the police. {Oh yeah, just FUCKING CRIPPLE HIM FOR A FEW YEARS, THAT'S FINE.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.66,0:20:27.79,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm sure that will satisfy \Nthe florist's need for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.00,0:20:36.59,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Hey, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:38.92,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get in the car. \NI'll leave you behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.63,0:20:45.60,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Mista! Do you want a ride or not? \NAre you taking a leak?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:48.64,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'm not! Yes, I want a ride! \NI'll be right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:54.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What's been bothering you, Mista?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.28,0:20:59.73,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Well, something about\N that guy's story just seems off to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.73,0:21:02.49,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,When he said his daughter\Njumped off the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.49,0:21:05.93,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...he mentioned she was \Nholding some kind of stone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.93,0:21:09.28,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Did he say what kind of stone it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:10.12,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.12,0:21:12.25,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Like, the shape of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.25,0:21:16.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,How big was it? \NThe boyfriend is a sculptor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.97,0:21:20.18,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He said it looked strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.18,0:21:24.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,But what exactly about it \Nmade it look strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.76,0:21:28.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He just said it looked strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.25,0:21:30.35,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What are you getting at, Mista?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.68,0:21:35.19,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,{\pos(1100,1055)}Wait, that stone back there...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.32,0:21:44.69,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,S-Stop the car for a second, Fugo! \NStop the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.69,0:21:45.35,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Why?
